She made the clarification while responding to a supplementary question from Siha MP, Dr Godwin Mollel, who wanted to know measures that the government is undertaking to solve the shortage of drugs during the Question and Answer session in Parliament. She said the government has invested heavily in the health sector, specifically on drugs, hence there are enough stocks in all districts, including Siha in Kilimanjaro. She argued the MP to raise current issues and not rely on past information. The Parliament business kicked off in Dodoma, today.